{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2023}} {{Infobox company | name = SLR Consulting Ltd | logo = 2023 SLR Logo.jpg | type = [[Private limited company]] | foundation = 1994 | location = [[Buckinghamshire]], United Kingdom | revenue = [[Pound sterling|£]]150.8&nbsp;million (2019)<ref name="environment-analyst.com">{{cite web |url=https://environment-analyst.com/global/106655/riders-on-the-storm-2019-momentum-carries-slr-to-robust-2020|title=Register|url-access=registration|website=environment-analyst.com|publisher=Environment Analyst |access-date=2023-09-15}}</ref> | num_employees = Over 3,000 | industry = Sustainability consulting | homepage = {{URL|slrconsulting.com}} }}
'''SLR Consulting''' is a privately owned international sustainability consultancy with offices in [[Europe]], [[North America]], [[South America]], [[Australasia]], and [[Africa]]. In 2019, it reported revenues of £150.8 million.<ref name="environment-analyst.com"/> Its purpose is ‘Making Sustainability Happen’, which it achieves through its global team of expert advisors and technicians, who partner with clients to tackle some of the world’s most complex sustainability challenges. <ref>{{cite web |title=About Us |url=https://www.slrconsulting.com/about/ |access-date=2023-09-15}}</ref> Its ultimate owner is Solar Holdings Topco Limited.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-06-30 |title=Companies Register |url=https://companies-register.companiesoffice.govt.nz/ |access-date=2024-08-07 |website=Companies Register |language=en}}</ref>
==History== ===Founding=== The firm was founded as SECOR Ltd in 1994 by John Leeson, Alan Sheppard, and David Richards. After establishing the company in [[Oxford]], [[United Kingdom]], in 1994, David oversaw the growth of the business from a small UK operator into an environmental consultancies in the UK, with international operations across [[Africa]], [[Australasia]], [[Canada]], [[Europe]], and the [[US]]
In 2000, the senior management team completed a management buyout and the company's name was changed to SLR Consulting Limited.<ref name="businessweek">{{cite web|url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=12722158|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130118221445/http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=12722158|url-status=dead|archive-date=January 18, 2013|title=SLR Holdings Limited: Private Company Information - Businessweek|publisher=investing.businessweek.com|accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref> In 2004 they secured funding from [[Livingbridge]], who invested £4.85&nbsp;million as part of a £13&nbsp;million investment including other partners, and took a significant minority stake in the company.<ref name="thefreelibrary">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/ISIS+investing+in+brighter+future+for+SLR.-a0122306016|title=ISIS investing in brighter future for SLR. - Free Online Library|publisher=thefreelibrary.com|accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref> In 2008, [[3i]] invested £32.5&nbsp;million in the firm, and replaced [[Livingbridge]] with a significant minority stake.<ref name="cleantechinvestor">{{cite web|url=http://www.cleantechinvestor.com/portal/mainmenucomp/companiess/1870-slr-holdings/7700-isis-divestment-of-slr-holdings.html|title=ISIS Divestment of SLR Holdings|publisher=cleantechinvestor.com|accessdate=2014-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140224222430/http://www.cleantechinvestor.com/portal/mainmenucomp/companiess/1870-slr-holdings/7700-isis-divestment-of-slr-holdings.html|archive-date=2014-02-24|url-status=dead}}</ref> In March 2018, [[Charterhouse Capital Partners|Charterhouse Capital Partners (CCP)]] acquired a majority shareholding in the business.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2018-03-26 |title=Charterhouse acquires 3i-backed SLR {{!}} Unquote |url=https://www.unquote.com/uk/official-record/3009224/charterhouse-acquires-3i-backed-slr |access-date=2023-07-30 |website=www.unquote.com |language=en}}</ref> In June 2022 Charterhouse Capital Partners agreed to a sale of SLR Consulting to [[Ares Management]] private equity partners.<ref>{{cite web |title=Charterhouse agrees to sale of SLR Consulting to Ares management |url=https://www.slrconsulting.com/news/charterhouse-capital-partners-agrees-to-sale-of-slr-consulting-to-ares-management/ |access-date=2023-09-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Charterhouse agrees sale of SLR Consulting to Ares Management |url=https://environment-analyst.com/108148/charterhouse-agrees-sale-of-slr-to-ares-management |access-date=2023-11-08 |website=Environment Analyst Global |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Wansboro |first=David |date=2022-06-20 |title=Ares Management buys SLR Consulting from Charterhouse {{!}} PE Hub |language=en-US |work=PE Hub |url=https://www.pehub.com/ares-management-buys-slr-consulting-from-charterhouse/ |access-date=2023-11-08}}</ref>
David Richards was Chief Executive Officer from 1994–2013. In line with the Group's succession plans, Neil Penhall, formerly Managing Director of SLR Consulting and an Executive Director of SLR Management, assumed the role of CEO.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Dunton |first=Jim |date=2013-11-18 |title=Planning consultancy chief dies at 55 |url=https://www.planningresource.co.uk/article/1221337/planning-consultancy-chief-dies-55 |access-date=2023-07-30 |website=www.planningresource.co.uk |language=en}}</ref>
===Expansion=== Over the years the firm has expanded its offices, with additions across Europe (including the UK & Ireland, France, Germany, and the Netherlands), Africa (including Ghana, Namibia and South Africa), Asia-Pacific (including Australia, New Zealand and Singapore), and the US, Canada, & Chile in the Americas. By 2023 there were more than 100 offices across 15 countries, with over 3,000 staff.<ref>{{cite web |title=SLR Locations |url=https://www.slrconsulting.com/about/locations/ |access-date=2023-09-15}}</ref>
SLR has made a number of acquisitions, beginning with the UK-based Waste Management Engineering Limited in 2005. Then followed the UK-based landscape architect company Insite Environments;<ref name="planningresource">{{cite web|url=http://www.planningresource.co.uk/news/664677/SLR-increases-masterplanning-services-Insite-acquisition/|title=SLR increases masterplanning services with Insite acquisition &#124; Planning Resource|publisher=planningresource.co.uk|accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref> the Canadian company SEACOR Environmental Inc.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bcbusinessonline.ca/files/files/BCB0411_SLR2.pdf |title=SEACOR Environmental Inc. |accessdate=June 8, 2012}} {{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> the UK-based company FMH Consulting Engineers;<ref name="environment-analyst">{{cite web|url=http://environment-analyst.com/124|title=Environment Analyst &#124; SLR acquires Bath-based consulting engineers FMH|publisher=environment-analyst.com|accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref> the Irish Dublin-based environmental consultancy CSA;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.endsreport.com/downloads/ENDS_CMG_2008.pdf |title=Consultancy Market Guide 2008 |publisher=Endsreprot.com |accessdate=2014-03-07}}</ref> the specialist mineral planning, landscape and land management firm Bowman Planton;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://environment-analyst.com/1042/slr-acquires-two-waste-consultancies |date=December 11, 2008 |title=SLR acquires two waste consultancies |accessdate=July 22, 2017}}</ref> the UK based Architecture and Planning Solutions<ref name="environment-analyst2">{{cite web|url=http://environment-analyst.com/1042/slr-acquires-two-waste-consultancies|title=Environment Analyst &#124; SLR acquires two waste consultancies|publisher=environment-analyst.com|accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref> Alaska-based Hoefler Consulting Group;<ref name="gecpress">{{cite web|url=http://www.gecpress.com/generational-equity-announces-sale-of-hoefler-consulting-group-to-slr-international-corporation/|title=Generational Equity Announces Sale of Hoefler Consulting Group to SLR International Corporation|publisher=Gecpress.com|accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref> Australia-based Heggies Pty Limited;<ref name="growthbusiness">{{cite web|url=http://www.growthbusiness.co.uk/news/mergers-and-acquisitions/1200238/3ibacked-slr-buys-heggies.thtml|title=3i-backed SLR buys Heggies &#124; Environmental consultancy in Australian acquisition|date=22 February 2010 |publisher=growthbusiness.co.uk|accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref> UK-based company Andrew McCarthy Associates;<ref name="thisisexeter">{{cite web|url=http://www.thisisexeter.co.uk/Environmental-firms-combine-power/story-11801791-detail/story.html|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130505143037/http://www.thisisexeter.co.uk/Environmental-firms-combine-power/story-11801791-detail/story.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2013-05-05|title=Environmental firms combine their power &#124; Exeter Express and Echo|publisher=thisisexeter.co.uk|accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref> South African based GreenEng<ref name="ebionline">{{cite web|url=http://ebionline.org/news-wire/843-slr-consulting-continues-move-into-south-africa|title=Environmental Business International|publisher=ebionline.org|accessdate=2014-02-20}}{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and Metago.<ref name="theengineer">{{cite web|url=http://www.theengineer.co.uk/sectors/energy-and-environment/slr-acquires-environmental-mining-consultant-metago/1007843.article|title=SLR acquires environmental mining consultant Metago &#124; News &#124; The Engineer|publisher=theengineer.co.uk|accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref> In Namibia it acquired Bittner Water Consult CC, a sustainable groundwater consulting firm,<ref name="nebusiness">{{cite web|url=http://www.nebusiness.co.uk/business-news/latest-business-news/2011/12/05/environment-firm-slr-consulting-expands-in-africa-51140-29893472/|title=Environment firm SLR Consulting expands in Africa - The Journal|publisher=nebusiness.co.uk|accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref> and A Speiser Environmental Consultants, a Namibian-based specialist consultancy with expertise in EIAs.<ref name="environment-analyst3">{{cite web|url=http://environment-analyst.com/4558/slr-acquires-second-namibian-enviro-consultancy|title=Environment Analyst &#124; SLR acquires second Namibian enviro consultancy|publisher=environment-analyst.com|accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref> In October 2013, Cooper Partnership - Chartered Landscape Architects was acquired in Bristol, UK; and in early 2014, the acquisition of HFP Acoustical was completed, adding offices in Calgary, Alberta and Houston, Texas. In July 2014 South African-based consultancy CCA Environmental Pty (Ltd) was also acquired. In November 2014 SLR acquired the UK-based oil and gas solutions provider Challenge Energy,<ref name="consultancy.uk">{{cite web|url=http://www.consultancy.uk/news/1076/environmental-consultancy-slr-buys-challenge-energy|title=Consultancy.uk &#124; Environmental consultancy SLR buys Challenge Energy|date=21 November 2014 |publisher=consultancy.uk|accessdate=2017-07-22}}</ref> and in February 2015 SLR acquired E.Vironment LLC, a Houston-based environmental management, health and safety, [[process safety]], and transaction advisory firm.<ref name="businessmag.co.uk">{{cite web|url=http://www.businessmag.co.uk/oxford-slr-consulting-acquires-e-vironment/|title=Business Mag &#124; Oxford: SLR Consulting acquires E.Vironment|date=12 February 2015 |publisher=businessmag.co.uk|accessdate=2017-07-20}}</ref> In April 2019, SLR acquired Novus Environmental, a Canadian specialized environmental firm.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Charterhouse backed SLR Consulting acquires Novus Environmental - Private Capital Journal |url=https://privatecapitaljournal.com/charterhouse-backed-slr-consulting-acquires/ |access-date=2023-11-08 |website=privatecapitaljournal.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=SLR acquires Canadian environmental specialist |url=https://environment-analyst.com/76779/slr-acquires-canadian-environmental-specialist |access-date=2023-11-08 |website=Environment Analyst Global |language=en}}</ref>
