{{term|term=[[Alpha particle]]|content='''[[Alpha particle]]'''}}{{defn|defn=Alpha particles consist of two [[proton]]s and two [[neutron]]s bound together into a particle identical to a [[helium-4]] [[atomic nucleus|nucleus]]. They are generally produced in the process of [[alpha decay]], but may also be produced in other ways. Alpha particles are named after the first letter in the [[Greek alphabet]], [[Alpha|α]].}}
