{{term|term=[[Concave lens]]|content='''[[Concave lens]]'''}}{{defn|defn=Lenses are classified by the curvature of the two optical surfaces. A lens is ''biconvex'' (or ''double convex'', or just ''convex'') if both surfaces are [[wikt:convex|convex]]. If both surfaces have the same radius of curvature, the lens is ''equiconvex''. A lens with two [[wikt:concave|concave]] surfaces is ''biconcave'' (or just ''concave''). If one of the surfaces is flat, the lens is ''plano-convex'' or ''plano-concave'' depending on the curvature of the other surface. A lens with one convex and one concave side is ''convex-concave'' or ''meniscus''.}}
