{{term|term=[[Crystallization]]|content='''[[Crystallization]]'''}}{{defn|defn=''Crystallization'' is the (natural or artificial) process by which a solid forms, where the atoms or molecules are highly organized into a structure known as a [[crystal]]. Some of the ways by which crystals form are [[precipitation (chemistry)|precipitating]] from a [[solution (chemistry)|solution]], [[freezing]], or more rarely [[deposition (physics)|deposition]] directly from a [[gas]]. Attributes of the resulting crystal depend largely on factors such as temperature, air pressure, and in the case of liquid crystals, time of fluid evaporation.}}
