The [[SI unit]] of particle displacement is the [[meter]] (m). In most cases this is a [[longitudinal wave]] of pressure (such as [[sound]]), but it can also be a [[transverse wave]], such as the [[oscillation|vibration]] of a taut string. In the case of a [[sound wave]] travelling through [[air]], the particle displacement is evident in the [[oscillation]]s of air [[molecule]]s with, and against, the direction in which the sound wave is travelling.<ref>
