{{term|term='''[[Surface tension]]'''}}{{defn|defn=is the tendency of [[liquid]] surfaces at rest to shrink into the minimum [[surface area]] possible. Surface tension is what allows objects with a higher density than water to float on a water surface without becoming even partly submerged.}}
