{{term|term='''[[Supersaturation]]'''}}{{defn|defn=Supersaturation occurs with a [[chemical solution]] when the concentration of a [[solute]] exceeds the concentration specified by the value equilibrium [[solubility]]. Most commonly the term is applied to a solution of a solid in a liquid. A supersaturated solution is in a [[metastable]] state; it may be brought to equilibrium by forcing the excess of solute to separate from the solution. The term can also  be applied to a mixture of gases.}}
